CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) It is used to style and design web pages + selection .
CSS controls how HTML elements look, such as:
* Colors
* Fonts
* Sizes
* Spacing
* Layout
* Positioning
* Animations

👉 While HTML creates the structure of a web page, CSS makes the page attractive and visually appealing.

Why CSS is Used
Without CSS, a web page looks plain and unstyled.
CSS allows developers to:
* Change text color and size
* Add background colors and images
* Create layouts (rows, columns)
* Make responsive designs for different devices
* Improve user experience

Types of CSS:
Inline CSS
Applied directly inside an HTML element.

<p style="color: red;">Hello World</p>
Used for small or quick changes.

Internal CSS
Written inside the <style> tag in the <head> section.

<head>
  <style>
    p {
      color: blue;
    }
  </style>
</head>
Used for styling a single web page.

 External CSS
Written in a separate .css file and linked to HTML.

<link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">

p {
  color: green;
}
 Best and most recommended method.

CSS Syntax

selector {
  property: value;
}
 Example:

h1 {
  color: red;
  font-size: 30px;
}
* h1 → Selector
* color → Property
* red → Value


CSS Box Model 
In CSS, every HTML element is treated as a rectangular box. This box model helps control spacing, size, and layout of elements on a web page.
The CSS Box Model consists of four parts, arranged from inside to outside:

Content
* This is the actual content of the element.
* It can be text, image, video, etc.
* The width and height of an element apply to the content area.
Example:

width: 200px;
height: 100px;

 Padding
* Space between the content and the border
* Padding increases the inside space of the element
* Background color applies to padding area
 Example:

padding: 10px;
Meaning: 10px space is added inside the box around the content.

Border
* Surrounds the content and padding
* Can be solid, dotted, dashed, etc.
* Border thickness adds to the total size of the element
 Example:

border: 2px solid black;

Margin
* Space outside the border
* Creates distance between two elements
* Margin is always transparent
 Example:

margin: 15px;

🔁 Order of Box Model (Inside → Outside)

Content → Padding → Border → Margin

Flexbox & Grid in CSS
Flexbox and Grid are CSS layout systems used to arrange and align elements on a web page easily and efficiently.
They help in creating:
* Responsive layouts
* Proper alignment
* Clean page structure

