- [ ] JavaScript (JS) 
JavaScript is a high-level, case sensitive , platform independent ,interpreted programming language used to make web pages interactive and dynamic.
While HTML creates the structure of a web page and CSS styles it, JavaScript adds behavior and functionality.
- Behavior means how a web page reacts to user actions.
- Functionality means what tasks or operations the website can perform.

Why JavaScript is Used
JavaScript allows web pages to:
* Respond to user actions (click, scroll, input)
* Perform logic and calculations
* Validate forms
* Update content without reloading the page
* Create interactive features like sliders, pop-ups, and animations

